# CLAUDE.md managed section (AIC)

Read this rule when editing `mcp/src/install-trigger-rule.ts`, `integrations/claude/install.cjs`, uninstall or snapshot helpers under `integrations/shared/`, or the AIC-managed span inside `.claude/CLAUDE.md`.

## Boundaries

- **Only** these lines delimit the AIC-managed machine-editable region (regex semantics live in `integrations/claude/install.cjs` as `CLAUDE_MD_OPENING_LINE_RE` and `CLAUDE_MD_CLOSING_LINE_RE`):
  - `<!-- BEGIN AIC MANAGED SECTION — do not edit between these markers -->`
  - `<!-- END AIC MANAGED SECTION -->`
- **Do not** place `<!-- AIC rule version: … -->`, `{{VERSION}}`, or any other server or package version marker **inside** the managed inner body. Version bumps must not rewrite `.claude/CLAUDE.md` or force unrelated commits.

## Single canonical inner body

- The managed **inner** markdown (between the two markers when the installer wraps the file) is one string: `CLAUDE_MD_TEMPLATE`.
- **`CLAUDE_MD_TEMPLATE` must be byte-identical** (UTF-8, LF endings) in:
  - `mcp/src/install-trigger-rule.ts` (Claude Code bootstrap writes this string as the **entire** file when no markers are used)
  - `integrations/claude/install.cjs` (installer wraps the same string between BEGIN/END)
- Changing rules text: update **both** templates in the **same** commit, plus `.cursor/rules/AIC-architect.mdc` and `.claude/CLAUDE.md` per cross-editor sync in `AIC-architect.mdc`.

## Installer idempotence (install.cjs)

- **Skip rewriting** the managed block when the normalized interior between valid BEGIN/END markers **equals** the normalized canonical `CLAUDE_MD_TEMPLATE` (after the version-banner removal above). Do **not** rely on parsing `AIC rule version:` inside the interior.

## Uninstall / snapshot

- Helpers that detect “file is only AIC bootstrap content” compare the normalized file body (or post–marker-strip interior) to the same canonical inner bytes shipped beside uninstall (see task 262 `integrations/shared/claude-md-canonical-body.txt`).
